### 2000 Census

As of the [2000 U.S. census](/2000_United_States_census), there were 6,940 people, 2,873 households, and 1,881 families residing in the city. The population density was 532.6 inhabitants per square mile (205.6/km²). There were 3,108 housing units at an average density of 238.5 units per square mile (92.1 units/km²). The racial makeup of the city was 93.14% [White](/White_(U.S._Census)), 2.38% [African American](/African_American_(U.S._Census)), 0.19% [Native American](/Native_American_(U.S._Census)), 2.07% [Asian](/Asian_(U.S._Census)), 0.03% [Pacific Islander](/Pacific_Islander_(U.S._Census)), 0.56% from [other races](/Race_(United_States_Census)), and 1.63% from two or more races. [Hispanic](/Hispanic_(U.S._Census)) or [Latino](/Latino_(U.S._Census)) of any race were 1.41% of the population.

There were 2,873 households, out of which 29.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 47.0% were [married couples](/Marriage) living together, 15.0% had a female householder with no husband present, and 34.5% were non-families. 30.6% of all households were made up of individuals, and 13.3% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.29 and the average family size was 2.86.

In the city, the population was spread out, with 22.8% under the age of 18, 9.5% from 18 to 24, 26.3% from 25 to 44, 21.8% from 45 to 64, and 19.6% 65 years of age or older. The median age was 38 years. For every 100 females, there were 82.2 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 76.9 males.

The median income for a household in the city was $32,095, and the median income for a family was $40,643. Males had a median income of $28,160 versus $21,141 for females. The [per capita income](/Per_capita_income) for the city was $16,288. About 11.5% of families and 17.4% of the population were below the [poverty line](/Poverty_line), including 30.8% of those under age 18 and 11.3% of those age 65 or over.

## Education

The portion of Fort Oglethorpe in Catoosa County is served by the [Catoosa County School District](/Catoosa_County_School_District). [Lakeview Fort Oglethorpe High School](/Lakeview_Fort_Oglethorpe_High_School) is located within the Catoosa County district.

The portion of Fort Oglethorpe in Walker County is served by the [Walker County School District](/Walker_County_School_District).